How do I add elevation to a row composable, just tell me don't edit the file
</user_query>"}]},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"To add elevation to a Row composable in Jetpack Compose, you have a few options:

## Option 1: Use a Card wrapper (Recommended)
Wrap your Row in a `Card` composable:
```kotlin
Card(
 elevation = CardDefaults.cardElevation(defaultElevation = 8.dp)
) {
 Row(
 // your row content
 ) {
 // content
 }
}
```

## Option 2: Use a Surface wrapper
Wrap your Row in a `Surface` composable:
```kotlin
Surface(
 shadowElevation = 8.dp
) {
 Row(
 // your row content
 ) {
 // content
 }
}
```

## Option 3: Use shadow modifier (for custom shapes)
Apply a shadow modifier directly to the Row:
```kotlin
Row(
 modifier = Modifier
 .shadow(
 elevation = 8.dp,
 shape = RoundedCornerShape(8.dp)
 )
) {
 // content
}
```

**Note:** I noticed in your code you have `.elevation` on line 117 which is incomplete - you'll need to use one of the above approaches instead. The `Card` approach is usually preferred as it handles Material Design theming automatically."}]}]}}
